Thus, $f(x) = 2$ for $x = -3$, $x = 0$, and $x = 3$.  So, if $f(f(x)) = 2$, then $f(x) = -3$ ,$f(x) = 0$, or $f(x) = 3$.

Since $f(x) \ge 0$ for all $x$ ,the equation $f(x) = -3$ has no solutions.

We see that $f(x) = 0$ for $x = -4$.

